The paper deals with the problem of data compression, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of massive datasets and distributed storage systems suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The paper also discusses the design of lossless data compressors, which is related to information theory, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category. The paper proposes a new algorithm for data compression, which involves trade-offs between space occupancy and decompression speed, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DC (Data Compression) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses experiments that show the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
